            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">A natural language assistant for answering space and astronomy questionsâ€”anything from satellite tracking to physics concepts, astronomy facts, and general space exploration. Integrates LLMs with real-time data from sources like NASA and ESA. Modular CLI and web interfaces planned.</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/shivmishra76/ai-space-assistant" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">View Project</a>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-gray-700 p-6 rounded-md text-center hover:border-gray-600 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">Space Weather Impact</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">A C++ application that fetches real-time space weather data from NOAA APIs and models its impact on satellites. Features atmospheric drag calculations, communication degradation analysis, and solar flare detection with CLI tools and Docker support.</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/shivmishra76/space-weather-impact" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

